Morphological variation of amazon and sailfin mollies

In this study, I am looking at various populations of amazon and sailfin mollies across their native/introduced range to assess morphological variation both within and among the species. I am using the Pickle fish collections for my samples.

PCA analysis

In this analysis, I will compare the principle components after centering and scaling the data. A PCA analysis will help us determine what aspects of morphology influence the variation in our data the most without worrying about differences in scales/measurements. Currently, data consists of 28 Sailfin and 45 Amazon.

Will use the original raw dataset rather than any outlier-removed datasets.

Preliminary data inspection

I will first examine the data using box plots to visually assess any major differences. Then I will run t-tests and F-tests between the species for each characteristic to see what differences in means and variences exist prior to any correction for body size. At the end of this section, I will present a table with all characteristics, the mean for each species, the variance for each species, and the p results for the t- and F-tests.

Corrections for body size

The amazon mollies are on averages larger than the sailfin mollies, as shown in the t-test above. To ensure body size is not affecting our comparison of these characteristics, I will correct for body size in two main ways: 1) I will run an ANCOVA for each characteristic using standard length (SL) as a covariate. Each model will resemble: trait ~ species * size. This will tell us if the mean differences of the traits are driven by the species or by the body length. 2) To correct for body size with variance, I will regress each trait against SL and use the residuals in the F-test. The original residuals should express both negative and positive values. Additionally, I will run F-tests with the absolute value of the residuals and note any differences in levels of significance (i.e.if it was sig in one but not the other). need to figure out why doing this was logical again.

ANCOVA

  • first I will visualize the regression of each trait against SL for each species to check linearity assumption.
